    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-20T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-20T15:00:00-05:00" n="672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/693a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d672fn1">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, on the same date, to the Ambassador in France (No.
                        2471).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-20T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5173. <persName>Morris Hillquit</persName> of the Socialist Party in the United
                    States has applied for a passport to attend Socialist conference called by the
                    Council of Workmen’s and Soldiers’ Deputies of Russia and has shown to the
                    Department a telegram addressed to him by <persName>Tscheidse</persName>,
                    President of the Council, inviting participation by American delegates.</p>
                <p>Please ascertain immediately from the British Government its attitude toward the
                    conference; whether it will approve the attendance of British delegates thereto;
                    whether it is believed that the conference will be held under the auspices of
                    the Provisional Government <pb facs="0821" n="747" xml:id="pg_747"/> of Russia
                    and is therefore to be considered as official; and whether it is thought that
                    German intrigue is involved.</p>
                <p>Please reply by telegraph as soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
